        "excerpt":"Supplementary resources for the course are provided below. These resources include textbooks, research papers, and other materials that may be of interest to students.       Nine Formulation Of Quantum Mechanics -Daniel F. Styer           Postulates Of QM            Green’s Function - Erik M. Olsen                   Green’s Function Example                     Scattering Theory - B.Zwiebach                   Variational Principle         Frequently Used Mathematical Formula         Frequently Used Quantum Mechanics Formula         Pauli Spin Matrices Relation     Appendix            Fourier Transform        Relativity Proof        Kinetic Energy in Generalized Coordinates        Vector and Tensor Calculus        Numerical Solution            Statistical Mechanics Formula         Handbook Of Physics Formulas     Particle Physics","categories": ["lecture"],
